From f88d61530ab4be77d1ec5c1aaf5e84c57596cb88 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: charlesmamane26-sketch <charlesmamane1826@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 14:13:35 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 07/11] fix(mcp): file:// gate, Content-Length cap, Origin
 allowlist + Host pinning

MCP-01: browser_navigate / browser_tab_new called navigate with no file:// gate, so an MCP client (or a web page reaching the HTTP port) could read arbitrary local files via browser_navigate + browser_snapshot. Gate them behind allow_file_access (off by default), threaded through BrowserState; new 'obscura mcp --allow-file-access' opt-in.

MCP-02/03: the HTTP transport allocated vec![0u8; Content-Length] with no cap and emitted Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *. Cap the body (413), reject cross-origin requests whose Origin is not in OBSCURA_MCP_ALLOWED_ORIGINS (403), pin Host to loopback (anti DNS-rebinding), and echo only the validated Origin.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>

